Chelsea owner, Todd Boehly, has engaged in a hot chase for Manchester United star, Memphis Depay, including Cristiano Ronaldo in the summer transfer window to fortify the team for the new English Premier League season.
Todd Boehly, being in charge of Chelsea for the first summer, is curious about transfer deals in signing Raheem Sterling and United’s Cristiano Ronaldo. The negotiation with Sterling was said to be near conclusion, as the management is still holding talks with Ronaldo.
Barcelona are eager to let go Sergino Dest, right-back, and Depay, for a swap deal in engaging the services of Chelsea’s Cesar Azpilicueta and Marcos Alonso.
Barcelona had already taken Chelsea’s centre-back, Andreas Christensen, from the English team; as Chelsea let go Antonio Rudiger to another La Liga team, Real Madrid, in Spain.





